# MCP and API rules

- MCP and web API routes wrap the same engine contracts; parse inputs/outputs with `@tell/schema`.
- `tell_capture`, `tell_diagnose`, `tell_redesign`, and `tell_apply` are the public Cursor surface.
- `tell_apply` returns patch text and instructions only. It must never write to the user's repo.
- Web `/api/diagnose` may use deterministic subprocess output; MCP `tell_diagnose` may add taste when keys exist.
- All API failures should return plain-language state and preserve the offline report fallback.
- `/api/setup/*` and `repo-runner.ts` execute cloned repo scripts and are local-dev only.
- Keep `.cursor/mcp.json` registered as `pnpm -F @tell/mcp start` unless the package script changes.
